how to handle an employee who is looking for another job i have a strong feeling that a person who is in a management position with my company is looking for another job the person would be leaving at a pivotal time of year for the company although they have not formally said anything their work has become uncharacteristic and sloppy i don't want to trouble the waters but i need to look out for what is in the best interest of the business what should i do i think i am more interested in the fact of me replacing the candidate i agree they are not worthkeeping with their current attitude i would really have to have someone on standby to step in their position i understand they have the right to look for better employment but do i have to right to look for someone while they are looking confront them about their quality of work as of lately and question their commitment to the company the drop in work quality could be due to many factors though it does not necessarily mean they are looking for employment elsewhere ask them about it and maybe you will get to the root of the problem maybe they are unhappy about thing around the office and it is taking a toll on their performance just schedule a talk and if they are looking for other employment at least you will know for sure and can begin your search for a replacement ahead of time i would say communicating with them is the key ITV ISO 9000 Infantilism Graduate school Employment Unemployment Anarchism and capitalism Strategic management Dynamic Systems Development Method Infant baptism Customer relationship management Goodness and value theory 1957 World Series Economic inequality Trade union Liberal Democrats (UK) Microsoft Extreme Programming Abortion debate Gender-neutral language Corporate governance Social rule Call centre Plame affair Capital accumulation Information Technology Infrastructure Library Freeters Publishing Education in the People's Republic of China Non-native pronunciations of English U.S. presidenti